org.apache.ignite.ml.dataset.feature.extractor

Class Vectorizer<K,V,C extends Serializable,L>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.ignite.ml.dataset.feature.extractor.Vectorizer<K,V,C,L>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - Type of keys in upstream.
    V - Type of values in upstream.
    C - Type of "coordinate" - index of feature value in upstream object.
    L - Type of label for resulting vectors.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, BiFunction<K,V,LabeledVector>, IgniteBiFunction<K,V,LabeledVector>, Preprocessor<K,V>, FeatureLabelExtractor<K,V,L>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ExtractionUtils.DefaultLabelVectorizer, ExtractionUtils.ObjectLabelVectorizer, LabeledDummyVectorizer, Vectorizer.VectorizerAdapter

    public abstract class Vectorizer<K,V,C extends Serializable,L>
extends Object
implements FeatureLabelExtractor<K,V,L>
    Class for extracting labeled vectors from upstream. This is an abstract class providing API for extracting feature and label values by "coordinates" of them from upstream objects. For example BinaryObject can be upstream object and coordinates for them are names of fields with double-values.
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
